        <section class=3D"container tool-container mb-13 free-tools-text">
        <div class=3D" justify-content-center">
            <div class=3D"col-lg-10 col-md-10 how-to text">
                <h2 class=3D"">How to use our online Venn diagram generator=
</h2>

                <p class=3D"how-to__paragraph">Use our free Venn diagram cr=
eator to generate beautiful overlapping circle charts for your presentation=
s. Follow these steps to create symmetric diagrams free and easy:</p>
                <ul class=3D"how-to__list">
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item"><p><span class=3D"how-=
to__list__step">Step #1</span>: Start by giving a name to your diagram. Add=
 your text in the appropriate field and customize the color of the title to=
 match your brand style.</p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p><span class=3D=
"how-to__list__step">Step #2</span>: Choose between 6 different diagrams, i=
ncluding the 4-circle Venn diagram and the 3-circle diagram.</p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p><span class=3D=
"how-to__list__step">Step #3</span>: Choose a background color and add addi=
tional elements, such as circles, text, or images</p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p><span class=3D=
"how-to__list__step">Step #4</span>: Every element within the Venn Diagram =
generator, on the right-hand side, is editable. You can change the size, co=
lor, and border of your circles. Add and edit your texts, zoom in or out, a=
nd add different elements directly from the diagram editor.</p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p><span class=3D=
"how-to__list__step">Step #5</span>: Play around with all the editing optio=
ns until you obtain a result that you like. Once you are ready, you can dow=
nload the diagram as .PNG, .SVG, .JPEG, or .PDF. You can also share the dia=
gram via link.</p></li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class=3D"how-to__heading">How to use Venn diagram templ=
ates in marketing</h3>
                <p class=3D"how-to__paragraph">Venn diagrams have applicati=
ons in many fields, including mathematics, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Set_theory" target=3D"_blank">set theory</a>, and logic. Here=E2=
=80=99s how you can use them for marketing purposes:</p>
                <ul class=3D"how-to__list">
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item"><p><b>Market research.=
</b> Transform boring spreadsheets into data visualizations, organize infor=
mation, and compare overlapping markets, audiences, or other areas of inter=
est.</p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p><b>Competitor =
analysis.</b> You might use such a diagram to compare your services or prod=
ucts to other competitors. This will make identifying overcrowded markets o=
r unique opportunities within your niche easy. </p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p><b>Decision ma=
king.</b> Perform descriptive diagnostic, and predictive data analysis to h=
elp your listeners visualize overwhelming data with our simple Venn diagram=
s.</p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p><b>Product com=
parison.</b> Create illustrations to display the main advantages and disadv=
antages of your products/services compared to other companies. This will he=
lp you identify areas where your team should focus their efforts to make im=
provements.</p></li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class=3D"how-to__heading">Benefits of using Venn diagra=
ms</h3>
                <p class=3D"how-to__paragraph">Below are the main benefits =
of using them in your presentations:</p>
                <ul class=3D"how-to__list">
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item"><p>Visually organize d=
ata and make your presentations engaging. </p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p>Compare and co=
ntrast multiple choices within a data set.</p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p>Solve complex =
mathematical equations. Watch <a href=3D"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3D=
MassxXy8iko" target=3D"_blank">this video</a> for a simpler application of =
these diagrams in mathematics.</p></li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class=3D"how-to__heading">What is a Venn diagram?</h3>
                <p class=3D"how-to__paragraph">A Venn diagram consists of o=
verlapping shapes or circles to illustrate logical relationships between di=
fferent data sexts and text boxes that explain the data. The diagram isn=E2=
=80=99t just made out of shapes but also the area around these shapes.</p>
                <div class=3D"container">
                    <div class=3D"row">
                            <img class=3D"col-6 col-sm-4" src=3D"https://fr=
eetools.textmagic.com/build/img/venn-diagram/venn-example-2.png" alt=3D"Uni=
on">
                            <img class=3D"col-6 col-sm-4" src=3D"https://fr=
eetools.textmagic.com/build/img/venn-diagram/venn-example-3.png" alt=3D"Abs=
olute complement">
                            <img class=3D"col-6 col-sm-4" src=3D"https://fr=
eetools.textmagic.com/build/img/venn-diagram/venn-example-4.png" alt=3D"Rel=
ative complement">
                            <img class=3D"col-6 col-sm-4" src=3D"https://fr=
eetools.textmagic.com/build/img/venn-diagram/venn-example-5.png" alt=3D"Sym=
metric difference">
                            <img class=3D"col-6 col-sm-4" src=3D"https://fr=
eetools.textmagic.com/build/img/venn-diagram/venn-example-1.png" alt=3D"Int=
ersection">
                            <img class=3D"col-6 col-sm-4" src=3D"https://fr=
eetools.textmagic.com/build/img/venn-diagram/venn-example-6.png" alt=3D"Uni=
versal set">
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class=3D"how-to__paragraph">Venn diagrams have several c=
omponents:</p>
                <ul class=3D"how-to__list">
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item"><p><b>The intersection=
</b> represents the overlapping section of the diagram.</p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p><b>The union</=
b> represents the combined area of all circles within a Venn diagram.</p></=
li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p><b>The symmetr=
ic difference</b> refers to the areas of the Venn circles that do not overl=
ap. In other words, it is the union without the intersection area.</p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p><b>The relativ=
e complement</b> means the section of a Venn circle that doesn=E2=80=99t ov=
erlap with another circle.</p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p><b>The absolut=
e complement </b> refers to any area that doesn=E2=80=99t include that set,=
 a full shape.</p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p>Lastly, <b>the=
 universal set </b> refers to the area around the Venn diagram shapes. It r=
epresents the larger category of data in which the set exists. </p></li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class=3D"how-to__secondary-heading">What is a Venn diag=
ram used for?</h4>
                <p class=3D"how-to__paragraph">Venn diagrams are widely use=
d in mathematics, logic, linguistics, computer science, business, and stati=
stics. The most common ones are simple, but some may become complex as they=
 progress to over six sets of data. Overlapping parts of a Venn diagram rep=
resent data sets that have something in common.</p>
            =20
                <h4 class=3D"how-to__secondary-heading">Who invented the Ve=
nn diagram?</h4>
                <p class=3D"how-to__paragraph">The Venn Diagram was invente=
d by English logician John Venn and became popular in the 1880s. Initially,=
 it was called the Eulerian circle after the Swiss mathematician Leonhard E=
uler, who created a similar diagram. Some people still refer to the Venn Di=
agram as the Euler Diagram. </p>
          =20
                <h4 class=3D"how-to__secondary-heading">How to make a Venn =
diagram?</h4>
                <p class=3D"how-to__paragraph">Suppose you need a more comp=
lex diagram, like the 5-circle Venn diagram. In that case, you should consi=
der the following:</p>
                <ul class=3D"how-to__list">
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item"><p>Decide exactly what=
 you want to compare and add descriptive texts for each data category.</p><=
/li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p>Start creating=
 your diagram. The circle is the most exact shape for Venn diagrams, but yo=
u can use any shape that emphasizes your point.</p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p>Label each sha=
pe accordingly and also add explanations to the areas that overlap.</p></li=
>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p>For more clari=
ty, you can also add labels to unique areas.</p></li>
                    <li class=3D"how-to__list__item mt-4"><p>If two or more=
 shapes have elements in common, ensure that all of them overlap correctly.=
</p></li>
                </ul>
                <p class=3D"how-to__paragraph">Venn Diagrams can be hand-dr=
awn or created in most photo editing or document software.</p>

                <h3 class=3D"how-to__heading">Why we created this tool</h3>
                <p class=3D"how-to__paragraph">We created this simple onlin=
e Venn diagram generator to help you create better data visualizations. You=
 don=E2=80=99t have to sign-up for software or pay to remove any watermarks=
. The design of our diagrams is simple, making them suitable for presentati=
ons, MMS campaigns, and more.</p>
               =20
            </div>
        </div>
